  <chapter id="introduction">
    <title>Introduction</title>
    <para>
      EWD is a data structures library used by some of the
      <ulink url="http://www.enlightenment.org"> Enlightenment</ulink>
      subsystems. It contains implementations for singly and doubly linked
      lists, AVL trees, hash tables, and plugin manipulation.
    </para>
  </chapter>

  <chapter id="structures">
    <title id="structures.title">Data Structure</title>

    <section><title>List Implementations</title>
!Isrc/ewd_list.c
    </section>

    <section><title>Hash Table Implementation</title>
!Isrc/ewd_hash.c
    </section>

    <section><title>AVL Tree Implementation</title>
!Isrc/ewd_tree.c
    </section>

  </chapter>

  <chapter id="util">
    <title id="util.title">Utility Components</title>
    <para>
        The parts that fall into utility components ease the daily labors of
        programmers when handling common tasks.
    </para>

    <section><title>Plugin Loading and Manipulation</title>
       <para>
          The plugin functions enable programmers to easily load plugins from
          desired search paths without the work of accessing the file system
          and path searching.
       </para>
!Isrc/ewd_plugin.c
    </section>

    <section><title>Value Relation</title>
       <para>
          The value functions are intended to abstract common hashing and
          comparison routines.
       </para>
!Isrc/ewd_value.c
    </section>

  </chapter>

